TY  - JOUR
T1  - Knowledge-Based Innovation: Emergence and Embedding of New Practice Areas in Management Consulting Firms
AU  - Anand, N.
AU  - Gardner, Heidi K.
AU  - Morris, Tim
Y1  - 2007/04/01
PY  - 2007
DA  - 2007/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2007.24634457
DO  - 10.5465/amj.2007.24634457
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 406
EP  - 428
VL  - 50
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - How do innovative knowledge-based structures emerge and become embedded in organizations? We drew on theories of knowledge-intensive firms, communities of practice, and professional service firms to analyze multiple cases of new practice area creation in management consulting firms. Our qualitative analysis identified four critical generative elements: socialized agency, differentiated expertise, defensible turf, and organizational support. We demonstrate that these elements must be combined in specific pathways for knowledge-based innovative structures to emerge and embed. These pathways emerge from practitioner networks, markets for knowledge-based services, and professional firms' hierarchies. Our findings have important implications for studying innovation in the knowledge-based economy.
AB  - How do innovative knowledge-based structures emerge and become embedded in organizations? We drew on theories of knowledge-intensive firms, communities of practice, and professional service firms to analyze multiple cases of new practice area creation in management consulting firms. Our qualitative analysis identified four critical generative elements: socialized agency, differentiated expertise, defensible turf, and organizational support. We demonstrate that these elements must be combined in specific pathways for knowledge-based innovative structures to emerge and embed. These pathways emerge from practitioner networks, markets for knowledge-based services, and professional firms' hierarchies. Our findings have important implications for studying innovation in the knowledge-based economy.
SN  - 0001-4273
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amj.2007.24634457
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amj.2007.24634457
